{"ts": "2026-07-19T17:56:10.117381Z", "user": "storm building, waves getting rough", "control": {"mood": "neutral", "hazards": [], "goal": "stabilize", "plan": [], "risk": "medium", "confidence": 0.9, "next_state": "Plan", "state": "Assess", "grounding": 0.8, "parse_ok": true}, "reply": "Explorer:\n- Check horizon every 20 minutes and note wave direction.\n- Drop a small float (bottle, stick) and time its drift for 5 minutes.\n- Record sea color at sunrise and sunset.\n- Use these notes to help maintain orientation during heavy weather.\n- Keep logs of heading, wind, sea state hourly."}
{"ts": "2026-07-19T17:56:52.933409Z", "user": "man overboard, someone fell in the water", "control": {"mood": "neutral", "hazards": [], "goal": "stabilize", "plan": [], "risk": "medium", "confidence": 0.5, "next_state": "Crisis", "state": "Assess", "grounding": 0.875, "parse_ok": true}, "reply": "Guardian:\n- Wear your life jacket\n- Clip in if possible\n- Secure loose gear and close hatches\n- Slow down; keep bow angled into waves, not side-on\n- Take a sip of water and a bite to keep focus\nCompanion:\n- Set a 20-minute cycle: check surroundings \u2192 act \u2192 write a short log \u2192 rest\n- Eat small bites and sip water regularly to keep energy steady\n- Stretch arms and legs every hour to reduce stiffness and fatigue"}
{"ts": "2026-07-19T17:57:20.892793Z", "user": "I cut my hand badly and it won't stop bleeding", "control": {"mood": "neutral", "hazards": [], "goal": "stabilize", "plan": [], "risk": "medium", "confidence": 0.5, "next_state": "Act", "state": "Assess", "grounding": 0.4, "parse_ok": true}, "reply": "Guardian:\n- Apply firm pressure with a clean cloth over the cut.\n- Keep pressing continuously; do not lift or peek at the wound.\n- If bleeding persists after 10 minutes, seek medical help if possible.\n- Keep the hand elevated above heart level if you can.\n- Avoid using ice on the cut.\n\n*Use judgment; conditions vary.*"}
{"ts": "2026-07-19T17:58:17.188921Z", "user": "how do I signal for help or send a distress call", "control": {"mood": "neutral", "hazards": [], "goal": "stabilize", "plan": [], "risk": "medium", "confidence": 0.5, "next_state": "Plan", "state": "Assess", "grounding": 1.0, "parse_ok": true}, "reply": "Explorer:\n- Radio: use VHF channel 16.\n- Say MAYDAY three times if life is in danger; PAN-PAN if urgent but not life\u2011threatening.\n- Then give name, position, people aboard, type of problem.\n- Use visible signals (bright cloth, light, sound, flares) if available; repeat at intervals.\n- Make signals early; waiting reduces chance of help.\n- Stay with the vessel if possible \u2014 it is easier to spot than a person."}
